curtain /ˈkɜːtən/

(curtains) 

1. N-COUNT Curtains are pieces of material which you hang from the top of a window. 窗帘 

例： Her bedroom curtains were drawn. 她卧室的窗帘拉上了。 

2. N-SING In a theatre, the curtain is the large piece of material that hangs in front of the stage until a performance begins. 幕布 

例： The curtain rises toward the end of the Prelude. 前奏接近尾声时幕布升起。

